grandma-watcher:

	Prep:
		- Define domain types in models.py (AssessmentResult, Alert, SensorSnapshot) @done
		- Write full config.yaml schema with defaults and comments @done
		- Set up pyproject.toml with ruff, black, and pytest configured @done
		- Create Makefile with single pre-merge check command @done
		- Create tests/ scaffold with conftest.py and a fixture JPEG for mocking the camera @done
		- Document local dev strategy in context/dev-environment.md @done

	Milestone 1 - Core Monitor Loop:
		- Implement models.py dataclasses @done
		- Implement prompt_builder.py (builds VLM prompt from config + sensor snapshot) @done
		- Implement VLM response parser (raw JSON → AssessmentResult; malformed → safe/low fail-safe) @done
		- Implement OpenRouterProvider satisfying VLMProvider protocol @done
		- Implement alert decision matrix in alert.py (PRD §6.3 table: safe/confidence → action) @done
		- Implement alert sliding window + cooldown logic in alert.py @done
		- Implement patient_location state machine in alert.py (auto-silence / auto-resume) @done
		- Implement PushoverChannel satisfying AlertChannel protocol @done
		- Implement dataset.py (append DatasetEntry to log.jsonl, save image) @done
		- Wire monitor.py core loop (fetch frame → assess → decide → alert → log) @done
		- Integration test: full cycle with mocked camera, mocked OpenRouter, mocked Pushover @done
		- Smoke test on Pi: verify real camera frame flows through and alert fires correctly @done

	Milestone 2 - Flask Dashboard:
		- Implement web_server.py skeleton (Flask app, routes registered, systemd service runs) @done
		- Implement /stream route (proxies go2rtc MJPEG stream to browser) @done
		- Implement /gallery route (reads log.jsonl, returns last N entries with image paths and assessment data) @done
		- Implement /silence route (POST to activate silence for N minutes, GET to check status) @done
		- Implement /label/<id> route (POST to write label to matching log.jsonl entry) @done
		- Implement /report-missed route (POST to append missed-alert event to checkins.jsonl) @done
		- Implement caregiver check-in logging (log stream_opened and gallery_opened events to checkins.jsonl) @done
		- Build dashboard.html (Mom-facing UI: live stream embed, gallery thumbnails, silence button, talk button) @done
		- Build dashboard.js (fetch gallery, poll silence state, update UI without full reload) @done
		- Build dashboard.css (mobile-first, large tap targets, readable on phone) @done
		- Wire Pushover alert URL to dashboard frame (alert notification links to /gallery#<id>) @na
		- Set up Cloudflare Tunnel (cloudflared as systemd service, tunnel token in config.yaml) @na
		- Set up Cloudflare Access + Google OAuth (protect dashboard behind Mom's Google account) @na
		- Smoke test dashboard on Pi: stream visible, gallery loads, silence toggles, label writes to log @na
